{"id":"math140-lineval-cr001","cid":"MATH 140","topic":"Functions Cost Revenue Profit","subtopic":"Evaluating cost and revenue functions","difficulty":1,"license":"CC BY-NC-SA (Numberbender original)","instruction":"A firm's cost function is C(x) = {m}x + {b}, where x is units produced. Find C({x_val}) and interpret the result.","params":{"m":{"type":"int","min":8,"max":45},"b":{"type":"int","min":100,"max":600},"x_val":{"type":"int","min":5,"max":25}},"answer_expr":"lineval","steps":["C({x_val}) = {m}({x_val}) + {b} = {m_times_x} + {b} = {answer_lineval}.","The total cost to produce {x_val} units is ${answer_lineval}."],"tags":["business-calculus","functions","cost","linear"]}
